add

public void add(GeneralTree generalTree)
Add a subtree to the current tree. The tree will be placed in the next available slot, ie: childNodes.size()

Parameters:
generalTree - The GeneralTree to attach to the current tree

remove

public java.lang.Object remove(int index)
Remove a subtree from the current Tree. Please note that this method could be quite a devastating operation as all sub trees associated with the subtree at index index will be lost.

Parameters:
index - The index of the subtree to remove.
Returns:
The removed object is returned to the callee
